<br>
~~~<br>
<br>
Dalain shifted uncomfortably.  The pleasant airy parlor now seemed suddenly too small.  He was much too aware of Arawyne.  She sat across from him, one hand on the table, her eyes cast down, her fingers tapping the table silently.  He cleared his throat and she looked up.  He caught her eyes for a moment before she looked away.  Unsure of what to say or what he was supposed to say, he reached over on impulse and covered her hand with his.  She jerked at the contact but did not pull away, her fingers trembling under his as he squeezed gently.<br>
<br>
“Why didn’t you tell me?”<br>
<br>
She looked up again, her eyes flashing in anger.  Tunare take it all!  That he could still affect her like this after all these years…<br>
<br>
“What would it have mattered?  You had your life, I had mine.  You had no space in yours for me.  What space would there have been for me and a child?”<br>
